@startuml sequence_bid_request
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333

title Sequence Diagram: Bid Request Flow (MVP)

participant DSP as "DSP Partner"
participant GW as "API Gateway\n(Kong)"
participant RTB as "RTB Service"
participant Cache as "Redis Cache"
participant Campaign as "Campaign\nService"
participant DB as "PostgreSQL\nMaster"
participant Kafka as "Kafka Broker"

autonumber

== Request Phase ==

DSP -> GW: POST /v2/bid\nOpenRTB BidRequest\n(100ms deadline)

activate GW
GW -> GW: Parse JSON (1ms)
GW -> GW: Validate schema (0.5ms)
GW -> GW: Rate limit check (0.5ms)
note over GW
  Check X-DSP-Key quota
  100K RPM per partner
  Add correlation_id
end note

GW -> RTB: gRPC call\ngetActiveCampaigns()\n(with 95ms deadline)
deactivate GW

activate RTB
note over RTB
  Start: 1ms
  Budget: 95ms
end note

RTB -> Cache: GET campaigns:active
activate Cache
Cache -> Cache: Lookup in memory (1ms)
note over Cache
  95% hit rate
  If miss → query DB
end note

alt Cache Hit (95% of time)
  Cache --> RTB: CampaignDTOs (1ms)
  deactivate Cache
else Cache Miss (5% of time)
  Cache -> Campaign: gRPC: GetCampaigns()\n(5ms timeout)
  
  activate Campaign
  Campaign -> DB: SELECT campaigns\nWHERE is_active=true
  activate DB
  DB --> Campaign: 100 campaigns (2ms)
  deactivate DB
  
  Campaign --> RTB: CampaignDTOs (2ms)
  deactivate Campaign
  
  Cache -> Cache: Store in cache\n(TTL: 5min)
  Cache --> RTB: CampaignDTOs (5ms total)
  deactivate Cache
end

note over RTB
  Campaigns acquired: ~1-5ms ✅
  Budget remaining: ~90-94ms
end note

== Auction Phase ==

RTB -> RTB: Match campaigns\n(geo, device, interests)\n(5ms)

RTB -> RTB: Run auction\n(select winner by bid)\n(30ms)
note over RTB
  For each matching campaign:
  - Evaluate targeting rules
  - Calculate final bid (CPM)
  - Track impressions counter
end note

RTB -> RTB: Render creative HTML\n(get banner URL)\n(10ms)

RTB -> RTB: Build response\nOpenRTB BidResponse\n(3ms)

== Response Phase ==

RTB --> GW: BidResponse (JSON)
note over RTB
  Total RTB time: ~48ms ✅
  Within 95ms budget
end note
deactivate RTB

activate GW
GW -> GW: Add response headers\nX-Response-Time: 48ms
GW --> DSP: HTTP 200 OK\nOpenRTB BidResponse\n(1ms)
deactivate GW

note over DSP, GW
  Total: ~50ms P99 ✅
  Well within 100ms deadline!
end note

== Async Event Phase (Non-blocking) ==

RTB -> Kafka: PublishEvent()\nimpression.recorded\n(event_id: unique, non-blocking)

activate Kafka
note over RTB, Kafka
  This happens AFTER response
  sent to DSP (no latency impact)
end note

Kafka -> Kafka: Enqueue message\nPartition: campaign_id % 10

== Analytics Consumer ==

Kafka -> RTB: (time passes)\nAnalytics Consumer\nreads event\n(async, 100-500ms later)
note over Kafka
  Consumer group: analytics-impressions
  Offset committed after processing
  Latency: 100-500ms OK
end note

== Financial Consumer ==

Kafka -> RTB: Financial Consumer\nreads event\n(async, must be <1s)

activate RTB
RTB -> RTB: Check: already processed?\n(event_id deduplication)
note over RTB
  Use processed_events table
  + event_id in dedup cache
  Ensures exactly-once semantics
end note

alt Event not processed yet
  RTB -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
  activate DB
  
  RTB -> DB: INSERT processed_events\n(event_id)
  
  RTB -> DB: UPDATE campaigns\nSET spent_today_cents += price\nWHERE id = campaign_id
  
  RTB -> DB: SELECT spent_today_cents,\ndaily_budget_cents\nFROM campaigns
  
  note over RTB
    Check if budget exceeded
  end note
  
  alt Budget Exceeded
    RTB -> DB: UPDATE campaigns\nSET is_paused = true
    note over RTB
      Alert: campaign paused
    end note
  end
  
  RTB -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
  deactivate DB
  
  Kafka --> RTB: ✓ Committed offset
else Event already processed
  Kafka --> RTB: ✓ Skipped (idempotent)
  note over Kafka, RTB
    Duplicate event detected
    Safe to skip (at-least-once delivery)
  end note
end
deactivate RTB
deactivate Kafka

== Error Scenarios ==

note over RTB
  
  === Circuit Breaker Scenarios ===
  
  If Campaign Service fails:
  • 1st error: try again
  • 5 consecutive errors: OPEN
  • Return cached campaigns or default
  • Latency impact: minimal (fallback in 1ms)
  
  If Kafka fails:
  • Non-blocking (doesn't affect response)
  • Queue locally in memory
  • Retry when Kafka recovers
  
  If Redis fails:
  • Cache miss: query DB (5-10ms)
  • P95 latency: 50ms → 70-80ms
  • Still within 100ms budget ✅
  
end note

@enduml
